**GENERAL TERMS**
> - **Draw** - Every turn you Draw 5 cards from the Draw Pile (you can look what cards are still in it by hovering over it in the bottom right corner, but what you will Draw is random), if your hand already have more than 5 cards or is full (the standard size is 10), you will only Draw until the max; If you draw all the cards in your Draw Pile, the Discard Pile will be shuffle in to it and you will Draw the remaining cards, **you can do this only 1 time per turn**:
> - **Arithmetica (energy or mana)** - base maximum is 5, it enables you to play cards;
> - **Keyflare** – previously referred to as skey/silver key, this charges up your Posse or Rouse in Arc 2;
> - **Posse** - Unique ability, unlocked through story/side story chapters, that you can activate by filling the white circle with 1000 Keyflare;
> - **Aliemus** – the yellow ring around your character icons in the top left, it lets them use their Exalt (Ultimate) when full;
> - **Exalt** - your character's ultimate/burst,limited at 1 per turn;
> - **OE\OverExalt** - when the ring turns red and increases its base maximum to 200, unlocked through 8 copies of the character (1 base + 7 more).  
> Comes with additional effect(s) to your awakener's exalt;
> - **Rouse** - a once-per-battle use card, it provides instant Aliemus and a passive effect to the character.  
>   Can be obtained at healing tiles or through the shop, or through keyflare in Astral/Arc2 stages;
> - **Ecog/Revives** - Emergency Gnosis, you can use them if you hp reach 0 to get full aliemus for all units, full keyflare, a cleanse and full hp heal, these are a Max of 5 revives you can store, with 1 refilling every day if not at max;

**Gambling-related Terms**
> * **Awakener** - the characters you play with, sorted into 4 Realms;
> * **Wheels of Destiny\WoD** - the “weapons” of this game, you can slot up to 2 per character, but only one can be of SSR rarity, but if you have 15 Dupes of an SSR Wheel (E3+12) you can use it in tandem with another SSR;
> * **Dupes** - duplicates of the character or wheel, these range from e0-3 to +12
> * **E#** - Enlightenment #, characters have 3 (e1, e2, e3), each unlocking a different enhancement to their kit, or boost to the values of a wheel effect;
> * **+#** - Further duplicate rolls, these go up to +12, making the number of awakers or wheels needed to completely max them out 16.
>   The main point of these is that for characters at +4 you unlock OE, while at +8 the level cap goes up by +5, with +12 bringing another +5 to it.
>   For wheels, getting a SSR wheel to +12 allows you to equip another SSR on the same awaker;
> * **G(unit)** - Genesis units, or the ones with the grey border and live 2D Splash art.
>   In the lore, these are characters from different realities/universes, and will be abbreviated as g(unit name) (e.g. gtulu, ghelot, gdoll);

**General Card Terms**
> * **Prepare** - Card remain in hand (compared to normal cards that get discarded at turn end) and decreases in Arith Cost by the listed number after every turn in Hand, also activates if discarded and then drawn again;
> * **Retain** - Card remains in hand at end of turn instead of being discarded;
> * **Exhaust** - Once played, card disappears forever;
> * **Aftershock** - The effect listed under Aftershock activates when the card gets discarded, whether it be through end-of-turn or another effect;
> * **Fleeting** - Card disappears forever upon end-of-turn;
> * **Stagnation** - Increases card cost by respective number.

**Chaos:**
> **1)** All realms can use a second posse per turn, but the second option is random from 3 that you have unlocked (can’t select the one in use and the selected one will not be available for the rest of the stage), but Pure Chaos (only chaos units) can choose what posse to utilize from among your full pool and activate it 2 times (will still be removed permanently for the stage);
> **2)** Gains 250 Keyflare at the end of the turn;
> **3)** All Awakeners gain 5 Aliemus when using Posse;
> **4)** Lv 45 Account bonus: choose 1 of 3 Silver Relics (random) at the start of exploration;
> **Universal Bonuses:**
> **5)** Having a chaos Awakener in the team also provides 100% Death Resistance (100% is the max, so 1 or 2 Chaos in Caro team will only provide 100%); 
> **Bonus)** If you put a Chaos unit in a team with another realm, that team is considered Pure for the purpose of calculating the effects of Realm Mastery and the Realm Mechanics (as if you only used units from that realm), with additional bonuses:
> * **Universal:** Every realm that is mixed with chaos automatically get +100% Death Resist At the start of the exploration;
> * **In Aequor:** Increases tentacle base damage by 1% of Max HP for every Chaos in team; Chaos exalt also increases Tentacle Assembly (number of tentacles attacks for the turn) by 1 (Normally you will get 1 Stack after Exalt, while exalts by Chaos units gives you 2) and charges 10 Aliemus for all Aequor teammates;
> * **In Caro:** Chaos units exalting increases Embryo Fusion by 35%;
> * **In Ultra:** Permanently reduce enemy attack by 0,5% Max hp, increase all allies Strength by 1% Max HP, increase all Ultra unit's Crit DMG by 10% for every Chaos in team.

**STATS**
> **1) Damage AMP:** Stat Shared with the team, it increases the Base Damage of cards and exalts, the Fixed (so not the one generated from damage) Counter and Poison generation and gives more starting damage to tentacles;
> **2) Black Sigil:** increases the coins you get after a battle, to buy relics etc in the shops;
> **3) Death Resistance:** Stat Shared with the team, it triggers at fatal damage, retains 1 hp and halving the total Death Res value. Gain 2 Athrimetica and draw 2 cards next turn;
> **4) Aliemus Regen:** Refund some Aliemus after releasing exalt;
> **5) Keyflare Regen:** You gain Keyflare (to use Posse) equal to this value, multiplied by the cost of the card played by the character (if a character has 20 Keyflare and you play one of his cards that cost 3, you will get 20x3 Keyflare);
> **6) Realm Mastery:** specific buffs for each realm, as listed below (if the team is Pure, except for Pure Chaos, all effects are doubled):
> * **Chaos** – for every 1 point of RM, all units get 0.05 aliemus when you use a Posse;
> * **Aequor** – for every 1 point of RM, when a unit release an Exalt, there’s a 0.25% chance to gain an additional stack of Tentacle Gathering (number of tentacle attacks this turn, if this exceeds 100%, you can accumulate additional stacks.)
>   In White Stance, for every 1 point of RM, add 0.01% of your Max HP to the initial shield.
>   In Red Stance, for every 1 point of RM, the damage of the tentacle attacks triggered by active damage is increased by 0.02%;
> * **Caro** - for every 1 point of RM, the shield you get for the first Devour of the turn is increased by 0.01% of Max HP, and the temporary Strength by 0.005% of it (this is still boosted by the current missing HP up to 100%).
> * **Ultra** - for every 1 point of RM, you have 0.125% chance to get 1 Insight (0 Cost, get 1 Arith and draw 1, Retain) card added to your hand at turn start (if this goes over 100%, you can get multiple).
